[[ Talk:Anna of East Anglia/Archive 1]]
== Wihtburh ==
The article says she's first mentioned in the late 10th century, but then says she's mentioned in the ASC in 798. From a quick look in Swanton it appears she's only mentioned in F, which as I recall is quite late, so maybe that's the confusion -- it's a 10C ms recording a 798 event. If that's the case, I think this should be clearer in the text.
